1
00:00:01,110 --> 00:00:03,310
(Episode 74)

2
00:00:03,610 --> 00:00:04,610
CEO Chae.

3
00:00:04,880 --> 00:00:07,080
It looks like Kang Baek Ho
is on his way to meet Oh Jang Mi.

4
00:00:07,580 --> 00:00:09,780
Really? Get the car. Now.

5
00:00:23,600 --> 00:00:26,260
- Tail them. Quickly!
- Right.

6
00:00:44,220 --> 00:00:46,990
- Who is it?
- The Chairman is looking for you.

7
00:00:48,490 --> 00:00:50,660
Tell him I'll be right there.

8
00:00:50,890 --> 00:00:53,530
Gosh, what are you doing in there
with the door locked?

9
00:00:53,590 --> 00:00:56,960
How dare you talk back to me?
I said I'll be right there!

10
00:00:57,160 --> 00:00:58,330
Now, go away!

11
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:05,500
Ma'am.

12
00:01:09,640 --> 00:01:10,710
Listen,

13
00:01:11,240 --> 00:01:13,950
I can't talk for long right now.

14
00:01:14,250 --> 00:01:18,850
- I'll call you back, so just wait.
- You have got to be kidding me.

15
00:01:19,150 --> 00:01:21,750
I'm the one who makes the calls, ma'am.

16
00:01:22,790 --> 00:01:27,590
Should I send the photos to your husband?
Is that what you want?

17
00:01:27,660 --> 00:01:28,860
No. Please, don't.

18
00:01:30,430 --> 00:01:33,300
I'm not even officially married to him,

19
00:01:33,670 --> 00:01:37,700
so one wrong move
and I'll be thrown out with nothing.

20
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,740
Gosh, this is driving me crazy.

21
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:43,070
Then why did you stray in the first place?

22
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:48,050
You sound busy, so I'll hang up.
Go freshen yourself up and wait.

23
00:01:48,110 --> 00:01:52,120
- To answer my call at once. Got it?
- Hello?

24
00:01:54,350 --> 00:01:56,860
- Oh, dear.
- Mom.

25
00:02:03,390 --> 00:02:04,830
What am I going to do?

26
00:02:06,100 --> 00:02:08,630
I'm in some serious trouble.

27
00:02:09,030 --> 00:02:11,470
- What am I going to do?
- I can't believe you.

28
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:16,540
If you get kicked out, I go down with you!
Gosh, why did you have to cause trouble?

29
00:02:16,710 --> 00:02:17,740
Gosh, I seriously can't take this!

30
00:02:17,810 --> 00:02:20,250
You brat!
Even if you weren't freaking out,

31
00:02:20,310 --> 00:02:21,680
I already feel like I'm dying here!

32
00:02:21,750 --> 00:02:24,750
Just hurry up and go to the chairman.
And act natural!

33
00:02:25,450 --> 00:02:26,650
Gosh, my life.

34
00:02:27,550 --> 00:02:28,720
Oh, goodness.

35
00:02:29,620 --> 00:02:31,120
What on earth is happening to me?

36
00:02:31,960 --> 00:02:34,830
I only remember having one drink.

37
00:02:53,610 --> 00:02:56,980
Be careful not to let Kang Baek Ho notice.
He's a cunning bastard.

38
00:02:57,980 --> 00:02:58,980
Understood.

39
00:03:00,120 --> 00:03:03,350
Get on it now. This is our big chance
to catch Oh Jang Mi.

40
00:03:03,420 --> 00:03:04,490
We can't afford to lose her.

41
00:03:32,650 --> 00:03:34,250
Director Ma, get in.

42
00:03:36,050 --> 00:03:37,560
I'm waiting for someone.

43
00:03:37,920 --> 00:03:40,160
- You mean Baek Ho, right?
- How did you know?

44
00:03:41,590 --> 00:03:43,700
I'll explain on the way, so get in.

45
00:03:47,930 --> 00:03:48,930
Wait!

46
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:54,570
That's Oh Jang Mi.

47
00:03:54,910 --> 00:03:57,440
Oh Jang Mi. We finally got her.

48
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,210
That slippery little wench.

49
00:04:02,250 --> 00:04:04,820
Didn't you hear me?
I said I'm waiting for someone.

50
00:04:04,920 --> 00:04:07,350
Baek Ho isn't coming, so please get in.

51
00:04:08,190 --> 00:04:10,360
How did he know I was waiting for Baek Ho?

52
00:04:10,920 --> 00:04:13,420
Anyway, I'm busy. I have to be somewhere.

53
00:04:16,730 --> 00:04:18,330
I'm sure you are busy, Oh Jang Mi.

54
00:04:19,360 --> 00:04:20,370
Mom?

55
00:04:28,070 --> 00:04:29,270
Who's Oh Jang Mi?

56
00:04:31,340 --> 00:04:32,340
CEO Chae.

57
00:04:33,180 --> 00:04:34,250
What brings you here?

58
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:41,020
Oh? Seo Rin. Why are you wearing glasses?

59
00:04:41,790 --> 00:04:44,390
They're just my blue light glasses
from the office.

60
00:04:44,860 --> 00:04:49,190
But I asked who Oh Jang Mi is.
Why are you calling me that, too?

61
00:04:49,330 --> 00:04:52,930
Lawyer Kang was bothering me with nonsense
about me looking like someone.

62
00:04:53,630 --> 00:04:55,630
I was mistaken, sweetie. I'm sorry.

63
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:58,870
General Manager Kang,
were you heading out for work?

64
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,140
Seo Rin, why are you just standing there?
Get in.

65
00:05:05,980 --> 00:05:06,980
Go on.

66
00:05:24,800 --> 00:05:27,700
You said you'd explain everything,
and this is where you bring me?

67
00:05:28,400 --> 00:05:29,400
Have a seat.

68
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:33,400
Think of it as a favor, as I pity
Director Ma, the unrequited love expert.

69
00:05:33,710 --> 00:05:35,670
Excuse me? Expert in unrequited love?

70
00:05:37,610 --> 00:05:38,610
Baek Ho...

71
00:05:39,210 --> 00:05:42,010
is in love with someone.
Her name is Oh Jang Mi.

72
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:46,550
I know that. You think I wouldn't know
about the man I have a crush on?

73
00:05:59,060 --> 00:06:01,730
Yes, Baek Ho. I'm waiting for you.

74
00:06:02,530 --> 00:06:05,070
I'm being followed.
Jang Mi, you have glasses, don't you?

75
00:06:05,340 --> 00:06:07,940
Quick, put them on and for now,
just stand there like you're Oh Jang Mi.

76
00:06:08,040 --> 00:06:10,140
- To throw Chae Hwa Young off.
- What?

77
00:06:10,480 --> 00:06:13,380
- Chae Hwa Young?
- Right. My brother's coming to get you.

78
00:06:13,880 --> 00:06:17,120
Stand in front of the car, draw her in,
and buy me some time.

79
00:06:20,490 --> 00:06:24,060
What? You want me to take
Director Ma into the office?

80
00:06:24,360 --> 00:06:27,230
Yes, I think she's waiting for me
on the street across from the hotel,

81
00:06:27,290 --> 00:06:29,560
- so could you go pick her up for me?
- Why? What are you up to?

82
00:06:29,830 --> 00:06:32,100
Something urgent came up,
so I have to get going.

83
00:06:32,430 --> 00:06:34,670
- I'm counting on you.
- Okay, fine.

84
00:06:37,070 --> 00:06:38,070
This kid.

85
00:06:38,900 --> 00:06:40,470
Looks like what I told him yesterday
is working.

86
00:06:48,680 --> 00:06:51,020
This isn't exactly my idea of a date,
stuck in the office.

87
00:06:51,580 --> 00:06:53,950
Who cares?
At least I get to talk to you, Seo Rin.

88
00:06:54,990 --> 00:06:58,290
- Here, drink up.
- I guess this is your idea of a date?

89
00:07:00,490 --> 00:07:01,860
Let me say this again,

90
00:07:01,990 --> 00:07:06,030
I have no intention of dating you
or being in a relationship with you.

91
00:07:07,100 --> 00:07:08,330
You sound like a broken record.

92
00:07:09,270 --> 00:07:10,270
I told you, didn't I?

93
00:07:10,970 --> 00:07:13,040
I don't care about your feelings,
Director Ma.

94
00:07:13,170 --> 00:07:14,270
What is your problem?

95
00:07:14,570 --> 00:07:17,010
I already told you
I'm not going to marry you!

96
00:07:18,640 --> 00:07:21,150
Are you trying to get back at me
or something?

97
00:07:22,080 --> 00:07:26,820
Is this a taste of my own medicine
for when I stalked you?

98
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:31,520
You're right.
Just as you did to me before, Director Ma,

99
00:07:31,790 --> 00:07:33,190
I figured I'd try it out for myself.

100
00:07:33,930 --> 00:07:36,460
Unbelievable! You want to go there?

101
00:07:38,560 --> 00:07:39,960
I'm kidding. Just kidding.

102
00:07:40,930 --> 00:07:42,030
But I am serious.

103
00:07:47,270 --> 00:07:49,570
The patient is responding
to external stimuli,

104
00:07:50,040 --> 00:07:52,280
which means that parts of her brain
are starting to wake up.

105
00:07:52,740 --> 00:07:54,150
It's definitely a good sign.

106
00:07:54,850 --> 00:07:55,850
Ma Seo Rin.

107
00:07:56,780 --> 00:07:59,020
Your family is waiting for you to wake up.

108
00:07:59,950 --> 00:08:03,250
Not CEO Chae, who's been lying to you
and using you your whole life,

109
00:08:04,120 --> 00:08:05,590
I'm talking about your real family,
Seo Rin.

110
00:08:06,660 --> 00:08:07,660
So please...

111
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:10,330
Please, fight this and wake up.

112
00:08:13,360 --> 00:08:16,630
She's a friend I was very close to
back in school.

113
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:21,510
She got divorced young and has been
living alone with her mother ever since,

114
00:08:21,810 --> 00:08:25,110
and sadly,
her mother passed away unexpectedly.

115
00:08:25,510 --> 00:08:28,210
So you can imagine how devastated
she must be, right?

116
00:08:29,410 --> 00:08:31,680
She doesn't even have any relatives
to come to the funeral,

117
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:34,420
so there was no way I could
just leave her all alone.

118
00:08:35,250 --> 00:08:39,620
That's why I had no choice
but to stay all night with her, Chairman.

119
00:08:40,490 --> 00:08:43,530
Is this a friend CEO Chae also knows?

120
00:08:44,300 --> 00:08:45,300
Pardon?

121
00:08:46,060 --> 00:08:48,400
You and CEO Chae went to the same school,
didn't you?

122
00:08:48,930 --> 00:08:51,870
CEO Chae doesn't really know her.

123
00:08:52,170 --> 00:08:56,410
Just because you go to the same school
doesn't mean you know everybody, right?

124
00:08:56,770 --> 00:08:58,840
Okay, fine. That's enough.

125
00:08:59,410 --> 00:09:01,380
You must be exhausted
from being up all night.

126
00:09:05,280 --> 00:09:06,280
Thank you.

127
00:09:06,580 --> 00:09:07,590
Oh, my.

128
00:09:09,550 --> 00:09:10,590
Hello, Chairman.

129
00:09:11,160 --> 00:09:12,160
Ma'am.

130
00:09:13,560 --> 00:09:17,160
Aren't you the young man
who delivers our side dishes?

131
00:09:17,300 --> 00:09:19,860
Yes, sir.
I have the side dishes you ordered.

132
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:23,300
That's right.
I placed an order for side dishes,

133
00:09:23,370 --> 00:09:26,240
but with the funeral and everything,
I completely forgot.

134
00:09:28,370 --> 00:09:30,310
Why do you keep blinking like that?

135
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:35,080
I guess it's because I'm so tired.
My eye is twitching like crazy.

136
00:09:35,180 --> 00:09:37,520
Oh, dear.
I must be low on magnesium or something.

137
00:09:38,180 --> 00:09:41,620
Chairman, my mother was up all night
making acorn jelly,

138
00:09:41,690 --> 00:09:42,690
and she wanted you to try some.

139
00:09:42,790 --> 00:09:46,690
She made this acorn jelly from scratch?
That's wonderful.

140
00:09:46,760 --> 00:09:48,090
I'm not sure how it'll taste,

141
00:09:48,090 --> 00:09:49,590
but I brought some for you.
It's on the house.

142
00:09:50,700 --> 00:09:55,330
- I hope you enjoy it.
- Yes. Thank you.

143
00:10:04,640 --> 00:10:06,510
Here's the meat you ordered.

144
00:10:07,610 --> 00:10:08,650
Enjoy your meal.

145
00:10:11,950 --> 00:10:12,950
Beef brisket and...

146
00:10:13,380 --> 00:10:14,390
How's Jang Mi?

147
00:10:15,250 --> 00:10:17,320
I told you to act like
you don't know anything.

148
00:10:18,260 --> 00:10:21,390
I dropped off the side dishes, so I'm sure
she'll eat them and get her strength back.

149
00:10:21,860 --> 00:10:23,860
I miss Jang Mi.

150
00:10:24,130 --> 00:10:27,730
Jang Mi is so pretty.
Suk Hee misses Jang Mi too.

151
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,870
Mom, I want some meat.

152
00:10:30,130 --> 00:10:33,070
Okay, sweetie.
I'll get you the meat you like right away.

153
00:10:33,300 --> 00:10:36,570
There are veggies you like here too,
so make sure you eat a bit of everything.

154
00:10:38,240 --> 00:10:40,710
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

155
00:10:44,250 --> 00:10:45,850
I'm sure you are busy, Oh Jang Mi.

156
00:10:46,350 --> 00:10:47,350
Mom?

157
00:10:55,390 --> 00:10:56,560
Who's Oh Jang Mi?

158
00:10:59,200 --> 00:11:03,100
Why was Seo Rin suddenly standing there
wearing glasses?

159
00:11:04,340 --> 00:11:05,600
For one second, I thought
she was Oh Jang Mi.

160
00:11:07,810 --> 00:11:08,810
Could it be?

161
00:11:09,140 --> 00:11:10,470
(Restricted Number)

162
00:11:16,150 --> 00:11:17,150
Hello?

163
00:11:17,550 --> 00:11:19,950
Chae Hwa Young? It's me.

164
00:11:20,180 --> 00:11:21,190
Oh Jang Mi.

165
00:11:22,290 --> 00:11:23,290
Oh Jang Mi!

166
00:11:24,520 --> 00:11:26,060
My, you sound happy to hear from me.

167
00:11:26,620 --> 00:11:29,490
Last I checked, you were terrified
Chairman Ma would find out.

168
00:11:29,660 --> 00:11:30,960
Don't get cocky, Oh Jang Mi.

169
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:34,100
- You've got a lot of nerve.
- No need to get worked up.

170
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,230
I'm just observing for now.

171
00:11:37,770 --> 00:11:38,900
I called to warn you.

172
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:42,970
Depending on how you act, I might just
send an anonymous tip to Chairman Ma.

173
00:11:43,570 --> 00:11:46,110
A tip? Go ahead. Do your worst.

174
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:51,820
It's not just your life on the line.
Think of your family. No, your mother.

175
00:11:52,520 --> 00:11:55,590
Why are you being so reckless? You have
no idea how much you'll regret this.

176
00:11:55,650 --> 00:11:56,920
Wow, I'm so touched by your concern.

177
00:11:57,690 --> 00:11:59,690
Since when did you get so nosy?

178
00:12:00,020 --> 00:12:01,960
You disgusting cockroach.

179
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:04,630
Fine, Oh Jang Mi.

180
00:12:05,260 --> 00:12:06,900
What's your end game?

181
00:12:07,430 --> 00:12:09,330
- Is it money?
- Shut it.

182
00:12:09,830 --> 00:12:11,770
Do you think I'm
a money-grubbing parasite like you?

183
00:12:12,640 --> 00:12:15,170
You need to pay for all the evil things
you've done.

184
00:12:16,470 --> 00:12:17,610
What do I want?

185
00:12:18,040 --> 00:12:21,850
I want to see you climb to the very top,
only to come crashing down spectacularly.

186
00:12:22,650 --> 00:12:26,620
So you'll be crawling at rock bottom,
beating your chest over all your sins,

187
00:12:26,780 --> 00:12:28,250
and regretting it with every bone
in your body.

188
00:12:29,520 --> 00:12:32,760
Too bad. That's never going to happen,
so wake up.

189
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,030
Very soon,

190
00:12:35,260 --> 00:12:37,460
you will pay for your sins,
Chae Hwa Young.

191
00:12:37,930 --> 00:12:39,430
I'll make sure of it.

192
00:12:39,930 --> 00:12:40,970
Just you wait.

193
00:12:42,370 --> 00:12:44,400
Hello? Oh Jang Mi!

194
00:12:46,140 --> 00:12:47,570
The nerve of her!

195
00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:51,040
Stop hiding and say that to my face!

196
00:12:55,510 --> 00:12:57,720
Mom, I've been thinking.

197
00:12:58,220 --> 00:13:01,520
What if we show the Chairman the picture
of Oh Jang Mi and Ma Seo Rin?

198
00:13:01,690 --> 00:13:06,290
- Are they really twins?
- You saw for yourself, Mom. They must be.

199
00:13:06,820 --> 00:13:09,390
But it's weird, isn't it?
Why would they be living apart?

200
00:13:09,460 --> 00:13:12,930
For the Chairman, who's so obsessed with
bloodlines, to raise twins separately?

201
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:14,130
It makes no sense.

202
00:13:14,400 --> 00:13:17,100
- Unless there's more to the story.
- The Chairman is in his room, isn't he?

203
00:13:17,800 --> 00:13:20,800
- Let's go tell him right now, Mom.
- Okay.

204
00:13:23,210 --> 00:13:25,140
Tell him what, exactly?

205
00:13:25,740 --> 00:13:29,910
- Hwa Young, when did you get here?
- That you spent the night with a man.

206
00:13:30,310 --> 00:13:31,950
Is that what you were going to confess
to the Chairman?

207
00:13:33,120 --> 00:13:34,150
How did you know?

208
00:13:36,090 --> 00:13:39,420
What? What are you talking about?
Spend the night with a man?

209
00:13:39,660 --> 00:13:42,090
- Who? Me?
- Yes, you.

210
00:13:42,660 --> 00:13:45,800
Do you think playing innocent erases
the fact that you two were knocking boots?

211
00:13:45,860 --> 00:13:50,670
- Knocking boots? Did you see us?
- What makes you think you can play dumb?

212
00:13:50,970 --> 00:13:52,940
It's no use denying it, Yeom San Wol.

213
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:57,640
Hey, if you think you can shut us up
with these lies, you're dead wrong.

214
00:13:57,910 --> 00:14:00,640
We happen to know a massive secret.

215
00:14:01,110 --> 00:14:03,610
- What? A secret?
- That's right.

216
00:14:06,020 --> 00:14:08,750
Ma Seo Rin and Oh Jang Mi.
They're twins, right?

217
00:14:09,190 --> 00:14:11,790
Am I wrong?
How could they possibly be twins?

218
00:14:12,020 --> 00:14:13,520
But fine, let's say they are.

219
00:14:14,020 --> 00:14:16,160
So why are they living apart?

220
00:14:17,290 --> 00:14:21,200
- What?
- Don't tell me you abandoned Oh Jang Mi?

221
00:14:21,600 --> 00:14:23,200
Or did you steal Seo Rin...

222
00:14:24,270 --> 00:14:25,270
Oh my!

223
00:14:26,540 --> 00:14:29,170
So that's it. You stole Seo Rin.

224
00:14:30,040 --> 00:14:34,250
- Shut it, Yeom San Wol. How dare you?
- Mom, are you okay?

225
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:40,180
CEO Chae, why are you getting so upset?
If you didn't steal Seo Rin,

226
00:14:40,650 --> 00:14:44,420
- does that mean you abandoned Oh Jang Mi?
- I don't care. Get out of my way.

227
00:14:45,020 --> 00:14:46,090
Let's go, Hong Ju.

228
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:50,030
Let's go tell the Chairman
this enormous secret.

229
00:14:50,330 --> 00:14:52,700
The Chairman has a right to know this.

230
00:14:53,130 --> 00:14:56,530
We've even got photos, you know.

231
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:58,300
Right. Mom, I'm coming with you.

232
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:04,070
You just wait.
The Chairman will lose his mind over this.

233
00:15:11,850 --> 00:15:16,490
What do you think will happen
when he learns that Seo Rin has a twin?

234
00:15:16,750 --> 00:15:21,330
You'll be kicked out of this house.
You're done for, Chae Hwa Young.

235
00:15:21,390 --> 00:15:24,930
Your days of yelling at me
are over as of today.

236
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:26,600
Don't mess with me, Chae Hwa Young.

237
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:31,240
Fine. Go and tell the Chairman everything.
In fact, that's exactly what I want.

238
00:15:32,040 --> 00:15:33,040
What?

239
00:15:38,740 --> 00:15:41,810
Go tell the Chairman all about
how you slept with some random guy,

240
00:15:42,410 --> 00:15:44,210
and then you can say
whatever it is you want to say.

241
00:15:45,320 --> 00:15:47,380
Instead of talking trash behind my back
like a fool.

242
00:15:49,950 --> 00:15:51,120
Gosh, my life...

243
00:15:51,690 --> 00:15:52,760
So, how about it, Yeom San Wol?

244
00:15:53,190 --> 00:15:57,060
Looking at these photos must bring back
steamy memories from last night, right?

245
00:15:57,730 --> 00:16:00,600
The one getting kicked out isn't me.
It's you, Yeom San Wol.

246
00:16:00,660 --> 00:16:01,730
This was your doing.

247
00:16:03,430 --> 00:16:06,570
You sent that man to drug my drink,
didn't you?

248
00:16:06,940 --> 00:16:10,370
What are you talking about?
I have undeniable proof right here.

249
00:16:10,810 --> 00:16:12,140
And you're still going to deny it?

250
00:16:12,780 --> 00:16:14,950
You can make up excuses all day long.

251
00:16:15,210 --> 00:16:19,020
When the Chairman sees these pictures,
do you think he'll believe your excuses?

252
00:16:19,150 --> 00:16:22,550
What do we do, Mom?
We'll be kicked out because of you!

253
00:16:25,320 --> 00:16:26,520
My wretched life.

254
00:16:28,730 --> 00:16:30,860
This can't be happening.

255
00:16:31,500 --> 00:16:33,630
If you get on your knees
and beg for forgiveness,

256
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:35,900
I might just forget about these photos.

257
00:16:36,400 --> 00:16:38,640
And you'll zip that trap of yours
for good.

258
00:16:40,440 --> 00:16:41,440
Hwa Young.

259
00:16:42,340 --> 00:16:43,670
I mean, CEO Chae.

260
00:16:45,680 --> 00:16:47,010
On your knees.

261
00:16:47,640 --> 00:16:48,710
Both of you.

262
00:16:49,980 --> 00:16:50,980
But...

263
00:16:51,620 --> 00:16:53,420
- That's...
- You're not going to kneel?

264
00:16:53,480 --> 00:16:54,490
Fine.

265
00:16:56,650 --> 00:16:57,650
Me too?

266
00:17:01,630 --> 00:17:02,860
You're out of your mind.

267
00:17:11,600 --> 00:17:13,370
They said Seo Rin might wake up.

268
00:17:13,900 --> 00:17:14,910
What?

269
00:17:15,240 --> 00:17:17,980
When you asked me to come along earlier,
you were going to see Seo Rin?

270
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:21,610
Yes. I got a call
saying Seo Rin moved her fingers.

271
00:17:22,810 --> 00:17:26,180
That's the best news I've heard all day.
I should've gone with you.

272
00:17:26,420 --> 00:17:29,190
If you had,
CEO Chae would've caught you for sure.

273
00:17:29,590 --> 00:17:32,560
I'm so glad you realized
we were being followed ahead of time.

274
00:17:33,490 --> 00:17:35,160
So, don't I deserve some praise?

275
00:17:37,800 --> 00:17:39,360
You did a great job, Kang Baek Ho.

276
00:17:39,860 --> 00:17:40,860
And?

277
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:42,200
Thank you.

278
00:17:42,600 --> 00:17:43,600
And?

279
00:17:45,770 --> 00:17:47,100
I love you, Baek Ho.

280
00:17:48,110 --> 00:17:50,970
That's more than enough for me.
I don't even need dinner tonight.

281
00:17:51,580 --> 00:17:52,580
Oh, you.

282
00:17:55,480 --> 00:17:56,480
But...

283
00:17:57,510 --> 00:17:59,450
I heard Jun Ho said
he's going to marry you.

284
00:18:00,720 --> 00:18:01,920
How did you know?

285
00:18:02,350 --> 00:18:04,760
To be honest, I'm feeling insecure.

286
00:18:05,590 --> 00:18:08,160
Maybe that's why
I keep needing your reassurance.

287
00:18:11,700 --> 00:18:12,830
Don't be insecure.

288
00:18:13,160 --> 00:18:17,530
- You already know how I feel.
- But Jun Ho was your idol, wasn't he?

289
00:18:18,070 --> 00:18:21,770
When we first met, you kept reminding me
you didn't get to meet Chef Kang Jun Ho.

290
00:18:22,210 --> 00:18:24,680
Jun Ho was just my idol,

291
00:18:25,180 --> 00:18:27,440
like seeing a famous celebrity, you know?

292
00:18:28,150 --> 00:18:29,180
Then what about me?

293
00:18:29,450 --> 00:18:30,510
You, Baek Ho.

294
00:18:31,110 --> 00:18:34,120
To me, you're the number one man.

295
00:18:34,950 --> 00:18:38,490
My precious man,
my number one priority, forever.

296
00:18:41,530 --> 00:18:42,690
Thank you, Jang Mi.

297
00:18:43,860 --> 00:18:45,760
So don't worry, okay?

298
00:18:56,070 --> 00:18:57,140
What are you two doing?

299
00:18:58,580 --> 00:18:59,610
Hey, Jun Ho.

300
00:18:59,980 --> 00:19:03,780
I was just coming on strong
to Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

301
00:19:04,620 --> 00:19:06,950
I told you, didn't I?
I like Lawyer Kang Baek Ho.

302
00:19:07,550 --> 00:19:09,490
No, that I love him.

303
00:19:14,460 --> 00:19:15,490
Ma Seo Rin.

304
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:17,630
I'm in love with someone else.

305
00:19:17,630 --> 00:19:20,360
- Please, don't be like this.
- What?

306
00:19:20,830 --> 00:19:21,930
Lawyer Kang!

307
00:19:22,770 --> 00:19:23,770
Director Ma.

308
00:19:24,700 --> 00:19:26,670
Are you doing this on purpose
to make me jealous?

309
00:19:28,340 --> 00:19:30,270
- Excuse me, General Manager Kang.
- I admit it.

310
00:19:31,240 --> 00:19:34,010
That I didn't recognize your feelings
for me back then, Director Ma.

311
00:19:34,580 --> 00:19:35,680
But even so,

312
00:19:35,950 --> 00:19:38,850
- this whole show is going too far.
- It's not a show.

313
00:19:39,280 --> 00:19:40,580
I'm telling you, it's not a show!

314
00:19:47,420 --> 00:19:50,260
It's nice how you liven up the mood,
even during dinner.

315
00:19:50,930 --> 00:19:52,630
Are you that happy I bought you flowers?

316
00:19:53,060 --> 00:19:57,000
We have two grown sons,
but neither of them ever buys me flowers.

317
00:19:57,330 --> 00:19:58,770
You're the best.

318
00:20:02,970 --> 00:20:04,110
Honey, have you ever...

319
00:20:05,410 --> 00:20:10,250
had any wild thoughts about leaving me?

320
00:20:11,350 --> 00:20:12,780
Why would I ever leave you?

321
00:20:14,150 --> 00:20:15,150
That's absurd.

322
00:20:19,120 --> 00:20:20,290
What's wrong? Are you sick?

323
00:20:21,060 --> 00:20:23,030
Do you have some kind of illness?

324
00:20:23,230 --> 00:20:26,060
No, what are you talking about?
I'm not sick.

325
00:20:26,130 --> 00:20:29,970
- I told you it was just a silly question.
- Don't even joke about that.

326
00:20:30,570 --> 00:20:32,970
Because I'll be the one to go first.

327
00:20:33,240 --> 00:20:35,370
Yes, ma'am.

328
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,480
- This is delicious.
- Right?

329
00:20:38,540 --> 00:20:42,050
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

330
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:57,430
First, whether CEO Chae is really
my mother or not...

331
00:20:58,560 --> 00:21:00,000
I have to find out for sure.

332
00:21:03,830 --> 00:21:07,340
(CEO Chae Hwa Young)

333
00:21:08,210 --> 00:21:09,810
Is General Manager Kang Jun Ho
in his office?

334
00:21:10,070 --> 00:21:11,380
Yes, he's in his office.

335
00:21:11,910 --> 00:21:13,080
Shall I put you through?

336
00:21:13,580 --> 00:21:15,180
No, I'll go myself.

337
00:21:17,880 --> 00:21:18,920
Is this the Private Detective Agency?

338
00:21:19,920 --> 00:21:22,450
I'd like you to find out everything
there is to know about CEO Chae Hwa Young.

339
00:21:23,690 --> 00:21:25,560
When and where she was born,

340
00:21:26,320 --> 00:21:27,920
and what her life was like
in show business.

341
00:21:28,190 --> 00:21:30,790
Is there anything specific
you want us to dig into?

342
00:21:31,230 --> 00:21:34,330
Who is Kim Young Ho's father,
the child that CEO Chae abandoned...

343
00:21:39,640 --> 00:21:42,240
(General Manager Kang Jun Ho)

344
00:22:02,390 --> 00:22:04,660
No, never mind.

345
00:22:06,000 --> 00:22:07,600
You don't need to look into it.

346
00:22:08,800 --> 00:22:09,930
Just forget I called.

347
00:22:20,610 --> 00:22:21,610
Jun Ho.

348
00:22:22,710 --> 00:22:25,280
- How did you...
- How did I know?

349
00:22:27,020 --> 00:22:28,690
Before that, you should be apologizing.

350
00:22:29,250 --> 00:22:30,590
For abandoning me.

351
00:22:36,960 --> 00:22:37,960
So I was right.

352
00:22:39,060 --> 00:22:40,330
I was hoping it wasn't true.

353
00:22:41,160 --> 00:22:43,000
- Jun Ho.
- Don't you say my name!

354
00:22:44,770 --> 00:22:46,670
You don't get to call me that.

355
00:22:48,470 --> 00:22:49,770
The name you threw away...

356
00:22:50,440 --> 00:22:51,440
No,

357
00:22:52,380 --> 00:22:55,480
the name I was called while I was bounced
from one orphanage to another...

358
00:22:56,780 --> 00:22:57,810
is Kim Young Ho.

359
00:22:59,080 --> 00:23:00,080
Got it?

360
00:23:03,350 --> 00:23:04,350
Please.

361
00:23:05,120 --> 00:23:06,560
Forgive me just this once.

362
00:23:09,090 --> 00:23:10,090
Forgive you?

363
00:23:10,390 --> 00:23:11,860
I didn't abandon you.

364
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:16,170
At the time, I thought
it was the only way to protect you.

365
00:23:16,870 --> 00:23:20,770
I couldn't buy formula. Seeing you cry
from hunger, I had no other choice.

366
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:24,340
- Please believe me. It's true. Jun Ho.
- I told you not to call me that!

367
00:23:25,640 --> 00:23:26,780
Don't say my name.

368
00:23:30,610 --> 00:23:32,420
I carried you for ten months
before you were born.

369
00:23:33,380 --> 00:23:35,690
The joy I felt at your first cry.

370
00:23:36,490 --> 00:23:38,320
Your tiny little fingers...

371
00:23:38,960 --> 00:23:41,120
The feel of them on my cheek.

372
00:23:42,390 --> 00:23:45,260
The sound of your breathing,
your baby smell,

373
00:23:47,230 --> 00:23:50,930
even the sound of your hungry cries.
I remember it all.

374
00:23:52,570 --> 00:23:54,200
The day I left you behind,

375
00:23:54,970 --> 00:23:57,940
it felt like my heart
was being ripped to pieces.

376
00:23:59,140 --> 00:24:02,180
Every night, I regretted it
a thousand times over.

377
00:24:02,780 --> 00:24:06,080
As soon as I was on my feet,
I was going to come find you.

378
00:24:06,150 --> 00:24:08,850
- But...
- Stop! Just stop!

379
00:24:09,990 --> 00:24:10,990
Stop.

380
00:24:11,820 --> 00:24:12,820
That's enough.

381
00:24:13,990 --> 00:24:15,890
I don't want to hear
your pathetic excuses,

382
00:24:16,860 --> 00:24:19,600
- and I have no reason to listen.
- No, please listen to me.

383
00:24:20,830 --> 00:24:24,970
I wanted to at least see from a distance
that you were doing all right.

384
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:26,200
But...

385
00:24:27,570 --> 00:24:32,010
- Chairman Ma made finding you very hard.
- So in the end,

386
00:24:33,410 --> 00:24:35,280
your own well-being was more important.

387
00:24:36,150 --> 00:24:38,950
I have no reason to listen to any more
of your ridiculous sob story.

388
00:24:39,680 --> 00:24:40,750
The only thing that matters...

389
00:24:42,520 --> 00:24:44,090
is that you abandoned me.

390
00:24:46,290 --> 00:24:47,290
Jun Ho.

391
00:24:51,530 --> 00:24:53,560
You're saying there are
no photo studios in Wonpyeong?

392
00:24:55,830 --> 00:24:57,500
Okay, I see.

393
00:25:04,670 --> 00:25:07,110
This kid is definitely
connected to Chae Hwa Young.

394
00:25:12,350 --> 00:25:15,650
Excuse me, I need
the General Manager's approval for this,

395
00:25:15,820 --> 00:25:17,550
but Team Leader Jin is out of the office.

396
00:25:17,720 --> 00:25:20,220
Here, I'll get it signed for you.
Let me have it.

397
00:25:20,520 --> 00:25:21,830
Thank you so much.

398
00:25:26,400 --> 00:25:28,300
I'll never forgive you.

399
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:31,270
So just go back to the way you were.

400
00:25:31,870 --> 00:25:35,470
Slap me and keep bossing me around.

401
00:25:36,140 --> 00:25:38,910
- It'll be easier for both of us that way.
- Jun Ho.

402
00:25:40,110 --> 00:25:43,250
- I know you must resent me.
- "Mother?" You call yourself a mother?

403
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:46,280
I have absolutely
no desire to be your son.

404
00:25:47,680 --> 00:25:49,050
So stop saying such nonsense.

405
00:25:49,820 --> 00:25:52,420
Besides, I know you don't have
a maternal bone in your body,

406
00:25:53,060 --> 00:25:54,290
so drop the act.

407
00:25:54,890 --> 00:25:56,130
Please, just listen to me.

408
00:25:57,760 --> 00:26:01,630
There are too many prying eyes.
I can't openly claim you as my son.

409
00:26:01,830 --> 00:26:06,440
But I will make sure you take over Dream.
I swear I will.

410
00:26:09,310 --> 00:26:11,270
- Says who?
- Please...

411
00:26:12,110 --> 00:26:14,240
Don't let emotions cloud your judgment.
Just think.

412
00:26:14,910 --> 00:26:18,550
Imagine having Dream Group,
this entire kingdom, for yourself.

413
00:26:18,650 --> 00:26:20,820
Is that why you needed Ma Seo Rin?

414
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:24,220
Because there was no way Chairman Ma
would just hand it over to me,

415
00:26:24,520 --> 00:26:26,090
you were going to have us marry...

416
00:26:27,320 --> 00:26:29,060
so you could take Dream for yourself?

417
00:26:30,060 --> 00:26:32,400
That's it, isn't it?
You're using me to get what you want.

418
00:26:32,460 --> 00:26:34,930
That's not it.
Please, don't misunderstand me.

419
00:26:35,970 --> 00:26:39,700
I wanted to give it to you.
Only to you, my son.

420
00:26:41,640 --> 00:26:45,640
You were going to marry your own son
to your daughter?

421
00:26:48,950 --> 00:26:50,550
Then who the heck is Ma Seo Rin?

422
00:26:52,080 --> 00:26:53,780
Don't tell me she's not your daughter.

423
00:26:54,120 --> 00:26:55,120
That's right.

424
00:26:56,950 --> 00:26:59,160
Seo Rin is not my biological daughter.

425
00:26:59,790 --> 00:27:02,690
But she is Chairman Ma's flesh and blood.

426
00:27:04,660 --> 00:27:05,660
What did you say?

427
00:27:08,060 --> 00:27:10,600
So, Ma Seo Rin is the Chairman's
flesh and blood,

428
00:27:11,900 --> 00:27:13,440
but if she's not your daughter...

429
00:27:15,510 --> 00:27:17,770
then whose daughter is she?

430
00:27:28,750 --> 00:27:29,750
Right.

431
00:27:30,490 --> 00:27:32,420
You have every right to question this.

432
00:27:33,060 --> 00:27:37,190
Rushing to marry you, my son,
to Seo Rin, my supposed daughter.

433
00:27:37,660 --> 00:27:39,030
Of course you would find that strange.

434
00:27:40,500 --> 00:27:42,270
Why don't you just answer my question?

435
00:27:43,600 --> 00:27:48,040
It's not something I want to discuss.
And it certainly can't be made public.

436
00:27:48,370 --> 00:27:50,610
Stop playing word games and answer me.

437
00:27:52,610 --> 00:27:54,310
If you're really my mother,

438
00:27:55,680 --> 00:27:57,980
then tell me why you're trying to marry me
to Ma Seo Rin.

439
00:27:58,280 --> 00:27:59,280
What?

440
00:27:59,750 --> 00:28:03,120
Wait, so Kang Jun Ho is
Chae Hwa Young's son?

441
00:28:04,090 --> 00:28:07,190
Not now. I'll explain it all later.

442
00:28:08,060 --> 00:28:10,990
What is certain is that you're my son,

443
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:14,360
and Seo Rin is not my biological daughter.

444
00:28:15,070 --> 00:28:16,430
The child in that photo...

445
00:28:17,170 --> 00:28:18,370
was Kang Jun Ho.

446
00:28:40,160 --> 00:28:41,790
(The First Man)

447
00:28:41,860 --> 00:28:45,160
So you and Chae Hwa Young are after Dream?
Fat chance.

448
00:28:45,360 --> 00:28:47,860
I will never let that happen.

449
00:28:48,060 --> 00:28:49,900
Who is Jun Ho's father?

450
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:53,640
- Why are you asking me that?
- Then I'll find out on my own.

451
00:28:53,940 --> 00:28:57,910
- Who Jun Ho's real father is.
- Colored contacts? They're prescription.

452
00:28:58,110 --> 00:28:59,440
She was wearing glasses, too.

453
00:28:59,740 --> 00:29:03,410
Don't tell me Oh Jang Mi is
pretending to be Seo Rin.

454
00:29:04,580 --> 00:29:06,580
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
